  "text": "In the heart of Sun Valley, Idaho, where snow-laden mountains frame expansive skies, Studio Mountain’s H.M.L. project reveals itself as an extension of the land, rather than a disruption of it. Light pours through oversized metal-clad windows, amplifying the grain on white oak floors while illuminating the Italian calacatta viola marble with its distinctive purple veining. This interplay of light and material creates what designer Sierra Fox calls “visual harmony,” which, for her, is more so a narrative about permanence and impermanence in mountain architecture. The project negotiates between high-performance requirements and artisanal techniques. The tadelakt showers – employing a centuries-old Moroccan plastering method – is evidence of traditional craft remaining relevant in contemporary contexts. Custom millwork by local craftsmen from Oak + Iron Customs elevates the residence with tailored functionality and warmth. This integration extends to the chef’s kitchen, where a 55″ Lacanche range sits alongside Fisher \u0026 Paykel appliances. The challenge of creating intimacy within expansiveness was addressed through material layering – a strategic placement of textural elements like tumbled limestone tile against smoother surfaces to create perceptual depth, making large spaces feel appropriately scaled. This approach continues throughout the home, where the integration of natural finishes – reclaimed wood, nickel, flagstone, and roman clay – creates a material language that feels both welcoming and harmonious. The residence focuses on a broader discourse regarding luxury and sustainability within the context of mountain architecture. Where earlier mountain homes often emphasized rustic materials in visually heavy compositions, this project employs natural elements with a lighter touch, allowing the surrounding landscape to provide the primary visual impact through those generously proportioned metal-clad windows. For more information, please visit studio-mtn.com. Photography by Aimee Mazzenga. Leo Lei translates his passion for minimalism into his daily-updated blog Leibal. In addition, you can find uniquely designed minimalist objects and furniture at the Leibal Store.",
  "image": "https://design-milk.com/images/2025/04/studio-mountain-hml-21.jpg",
  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n                        \u003cp\u003eIn the heart of Sun Valley, Idaho, where snow-laden mountains frame expansive skies, \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.studio-mtn.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003eStudio Mountain’s\u003c/a\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://www.studio-mtn.com/hml\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003eH.M.L.\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e project reveals itself as an extension of the land, rather than a disruption of it. Light pours through oversized metal-clad windows, amplifying the grain on white oak floors while illuminating the Italian calacatta viola marble with its distinctive purple veining. This interplay of light and material creates what designer Sierra Fox calls “visual harmony,” which, for her, is more so a narrative about permanence and impermanence in mountain architecture.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=573589\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-573589\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/04/studio-mountain-hml-17-810x540.jpg\" alt=\"Spacious dining room with a wooden table and white chairs, large paper lanterns, exposed wooden beams, a stone fireplace, and natural light from large windows.\" width=\"810\" height=\"540\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/04/studio-mountain-hml-17-810x540.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/04/studio-mountain-hml-17-800x533.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/04/studio-mountain-hml-17-768x512.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/04/studio-mountain-hml-17.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe project negotiates between high-performance requirements and artisanal techniques. The tadelakt showers – employing a centuries-old Moroccan plastering method – is evidence of traditional craft remaining relevant in contemporary contexts. Custom millwork by local craftsmen from \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.oakandironcustoms.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003eOak + Iron Customs\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e elevates the residence with tailored functionality and warmth. This integration extends to the chef’s kitchen, where a 55″ Lacanche range sits alongside Fisher \u0026amp; Paykel appliances.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=573596\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-573596\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/04/studio-mountain-hml-8-810x1215.jpg\" alt=\"A cozy living room with a stone fireplace, a large mirror above it, two brown armchairs, a white armchair, a wooden coffee table, and a round paper lantern hanging from the ceiling.\" width=\"810\" height=\"1215\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/04/studio-mountain-hml-8-810x1215.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/04/studio-mountain-hml-8-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/04/studio-mountain-hml-8-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/04/studio-mountain-hml-8-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://design-milk.com/images/2025/04/studio-mountain-hml-8.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=573580\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-573580\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2025/04/studio-mountain-hml-32-810x1215.jpg\" alt=\"Cozy corner with a round wooden table, cushioned bench seating, abstract wall art, and a bowl of fruit. Large window with a view and two textured stools complete